						<summary>

						<p>Stone (No. I) lying outside the Kadaṁbēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Kṛishṇarāya A.D. 1524.</p>						

						<p>This damaged inscription is dated Śaka 1446, Plavaṁga, Vaiśākha. Other details of the date are not given. It seems to refer to a gift to an individual of Yaju-śākha.</p>						

